f(a,b)
 1) f(a+b,b)=f(a,b),\quad \forall a,b\in \mathbb{R}\\ 2) f(a,b)=\sin 2\pi ab,\quad  \text{if} \quad \forall a\in \mathbb{R},\forall b\in \mathbb{Z}
\sin2\pi ab
f(a,b)=0
b\not\in{\Bbb Z}
b\not\in{\Bbb Z}:\ f(a+b,b)=0=f(a,b)
b\in{\Bbb Z}:\ f(a+b,b)=\sin2\pi(a+b)b=\sin(2\pi ab+2\pi b^2)=\sin(2\pi ab) =f(a,b).
